@startuml
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName "Segoe UI"
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam activityBackgroundColor #F8F9FA
skinparam activityBorderColor #495057
skinparam activityArrowColor #495057
skinparam activityFontColor #212529
skinparam partitionBackgroundColor #E9ECEF
skinparam partitionBorderColor #6C757D
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFF9C4
skinparam noteBorderColor #F0C040

title Parallel SMT Consumer Processing

|Main Thread|
start
:processRecords(List<SourceRecord> records);
note right
  **ParallelSmtConsumerProcessor**
  transform only → Consumer<SourceRecord>
  ----
  **ParallelSmtAndConvertConsumerProcessor<R>**
  transform + convert → Consumer<R>
end note

:Log: submitting N records for processing;

:Submit all records as callables\nto ExecutorService (recordService);
note right
  Future<T>[] recordFutures = new Future[N]
  Each callable submitted independently
end note

fork
  |ExecutorService Worker 1|
  :TransformRecord[0].call()
  transformations.transform(record[0])
  → SourceRecord (or null if filtered);

fork again
  |ExecutorService Worker 2|
  :TransformRecord[1].call()
  transformations.transform(record[1])
  → SourceRecord (or null if filtered);

fork again
  |ExecutorService Worker N|
  :TransformRecord[N-1].call()
  transformations.transform(record[N-1])
  → SourceRecord (or null if filtered);
  note right
    **+Convert step**
    (ParallelSmtAndConvertConsumerProcessor only)
    convertor.apply(transformedRecord) → R
  end note

end fork

|Main Thread|
note right
  Worker threads ran concurrently.
  Main thread now collects results in
  original insertion order via Future[i].get()
end note

while (More records to collect?) is (yes)

  :Future[i].get()
  → transformed record (blocks if not yet done);

  if (record != null?) then (yes — passed filter)

    |Consumer|
    :consumer.accept(record);
    note right
      **ParallelSmtConsumerProcessor**:
        Consumer<SourceRecord>.accept(SourceRecord)
      **ParallelSmtAndConvertConsumerProcessor**:
        Consumer<R>.accept(R)
    end note

    |Main Thread|
    if (StopEngineException thrown?) then (yes)
      |RecordCommitter|
      :committer.markProcessed(originalRecord[i]);

      |Main Thread|
      :Re-throw StopEngineException;
      kill

    else (no — success)
    endif

  else (no — null / filtered out)
    :Skip consumer call\n(record filtered by transformations);
  endif

  |RecordCommitter|
  :committer.markProcessed(originalRecord[i]);
  note right
    Always marked processed,
    even if filtered (null record)
  end note

  |Main Thread|

endwhile (no — all N records processed)

|RecordCommitter|
:committer.markBatchFinished();

|Main Thread|
stop

@enduml
